          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make and blind bake the pastry case",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rub the butter into the flour and icing sugar until the mixture resembles fine breadcrumbs. Add the egg yolk and water and bring the dough together. Wrap and refrigerate for 30 minutes. Preheat the oven to 190°C conventional. Roll the pastry to 3 mm thick and line a 23 cm loose-bottomed tart tin. Press into the edges, letting any excess overhang. Prick the base. Line with baking paper and fill with baking beans. Bake for 20 minutes, remove the beans and paper, then bake for a further 8 to 10 minutes until the base is dry and pale gold. Trim the edges. Cool completely.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the pastry cream",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whisk the egg yolks, sugar, and cornflour until smooth. Bring the milk to a simmer, pour a third over the egg mixture while whisking, then return to the pan and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick and large bubbles appear. Remove from heat, stir in the butter and vanilla. Press cling film directly onto the surface and refrigerate until cold and set.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Assemble",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the cold pastry cream briefly to loosen it. Spread a third of the pastry cream over the base of the cooled pastry case. Arrange a layer of sliced bananas over the cream. Add the remaining pastry cream and smooth the top. Arrange another layer of banana slices over the top. Spoon or pipe the lightly whipped cream over the bananas. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving. Cut with a sharp knife dipped in hot water between slices.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
